WHEREAS, in 2025, Crimestoppers GNO worked alongside the Louisiana State
Police and other local and federal agencies to assist in the investigation of the May 16th
escape of ten inmates from the New Orleans Parish Justice Center; the organization offered
cash rewards and provided the public the ability to report several thousand tips
anonymously, which led to the capture of several inmates; and
WHEREAS, Crimestoppers GNO is affiliated with Crimestoppers USA and serves
a mission to provide law enforcement with information on crimes; these efforts increase
arrests in our community and lead to greater public awareness of safety issues and crime
prevention.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
commend Crimestoppers GNO on the occasion of its forty-fifth anniversary; does hereby
recognize March 2026 as Louisiana Crimestoppers Month; and does hereby encourage all
residents to participate in local Crimestoppers efforts to prevent crime and strengthen the
state's communities.
